1
00:02:23,240 --> 00:02:25,280
I'd rather die than not see Mr. Na.

2
00:02:25,360 --> 00:02:26,680
Let go.

3
00:02:30,800 --> 00:02:32,480
Are you considering a new plan?

4
00:02:32,560 --> 00:02:34,600
Yes, Uncle.
So that everything wraps up faster.

5
00:02:34,680 --> 00:02:37,480
<i>From now on, the sole owner of Paisal Farm</i>

6
00:02:37,560 --> 00:02:39,960
is Mr. Tatsana!

7
00:02:41,560 --> 00:02:45,480
In that case, I'll be at your service too,

8
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:46,840
Mr. Tatsana.

9
00:02:55,520 --> 00:02:58,120
May the divine powers protect Pin.

10
00:02:59,240 --> 00:03:02,360
Please keep Pin safe from evildoers.

11
00:03:03,480 --> 00:03:05,440
If my life is the price for this,

12
00:03:06,080 --> 00:03:07,440
I will gladly pay it.

13
00:03:08,160 --> 00:03:09,520
Aunt Un!

14
00:03:10,840 --> 00:03:13,840
Stop with your prayers.

15
00:03:13,920 --> 00:03:15,200
Pin is back.

16
00:03:15,280 --> 00:03:16,440
Huh?

17
00:03:17,080 --> 00:03:18,720
- Really?
- Yes.

18
00:03:20,040 --> 00:03:21,280
Lord Buddha, you've granted my wish.

19
00:03:21,360 --> 00:03:24,400
Ugh, Lord Buddha didn't help her.

20
00:03:24,480 --> 00:03:27,240
I think you should go help Pin yourself.

21
00:03:29,720 --> 00:03:30,760
Hey.

22
00:03:33,560 --> 00:03:34,680
Pin.

23
00:03:35,480 --> 00:03:36,480
Mr. Na?

24
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:45,240
Grab him. He's the culprit.

25
00:03:45,320 --> 00:03:46,320
Hey.

26
00:03:46,400 --> 00:03:48,280
Think it through, Manager.

27
00:03:48,360 --> 00:03:50,520
Do you really want the police involved?

28
00:03:50,600 --> 00:03:54,120
Since all of you, as well as Tong,
will be charged with the kidnapping

29
00:03:54,200 --> 00:03:55,920
and attempted murder of me and Pinanong.

30
00:04:06,040 --> 00:04:07,080
What are you trying to say?

31
00:04:07,160 --> 00:04:08,840
Madam Krongsuk

32
00:04:08,920 --> 00:04:11,320
planned to have Mr. Tong lock Pin up

33
00:04:11,400 --> 00:04:13,680
to lure Mr. Yai out there to help her,

34
00:04:13,760 --> 00:04:15,040
then planned to kill them both.

35
00:04:21,040 --> 00:04:22,240
Is that true, Pin?

36
00:04:26,640 --> 00:04:27,600
Yes.

37
00:04:28,240 --> 00:04:29,360
You're lying.

38
00:04:29,440 --> 00:04:30,880
Don't you dare accuse me.

39
00:04:30,960 --> 00:04:32,360
Why would I do that to you?

40
00:04:33,240 --> 00:04:35,360
To replace me with your niece and nephew.

41
00:04:36,200 --> 00:04:37,880
We're as bad as each other.

42
00:04:37,960 --> 00:04:39,320
I see through you,

43
00:04:39,400 --> 00:04:40,880
as clearly as you see the boobies--

44
00:04:40,960 --> 00:04:42,080
Oops.

45
00:04:42,160 --> 00:04:43,640
…see through me.

46
00:04:44,720 --> 00:04:46,680
What really happened, Auntie?

47
00:04:55,200 --> 00:04:56,440
What do we do?

48
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:01,800
Pin, my dear.

49
00:05:03,840 --> 00:05:06,440
You know how much I care about you.

50
00:05:06,520 --> 00:05:09,000
If I knew that Mr. Tong had taken you,

51
00:05:09,720 --> 00:05:10,800
I would have followed you to help you.

52
00:05:10,880 --> 00:05:12,520
You wouldn't have needed Mr. Yai.

53
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:18,240
Madam.

54
00:05:18,320 --> 00:05:20,160
I thank the sacred beings
of Earth and Heaven

55
00:05:20,240 --> 00:05:21,840
and thank Paisal

56
00:05:21,920 --> 00:05:23,960
for helping to protect you.

57
00:05:25,120 --> 00:05:26,840
Tong fooled me,

58
00:05:27,600 --> 00:05:29,920
trying to harm you and Mr. Yai.

59
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:31,480
May his downfall come quickly,

60
00:05:31,560 --> 00:05:33,680
starting this very moment.

61
00:05:34,280 --> 00:05:35,240
Madam.

62
00:05:37,040 --> 00:05:38,600
Oh, Madam.

63
00:05:38,680 --> 00:05:40,240
If your acting is this dramatic,

64
00:05:40,320 --> 00:05:41,760
should I get you an award?

65
00:05:46,520 --> 00:05:47,480
Take this.

66
00:05:47,560 --> 00:05:49,160
If you think it was me,

67
00:05:49,240 --> 00:05:50,760
then take your revenge.

68
00:05:51,360 --> 00:05:52,240
Auntie.

69
00:05:52,320 --> 00:05:54,080
No, Madam.

70
00:05:54,160 --> 00:05:56,320
I didn't think that.

71
00:05:56,400 --> 00:05:57,960
I believe you.

72
00:05:58,040 --> 00:05:59,720
Please let it end here.

73
00:06:00,720 --> 00:06:01,720
She's done, but I'm not.

74
00:06:02,760 --> 00:06:03,640
Please don't, Mr. Yai.

75
00:06:03,720 --> 00:06:04,760
Pan, move Pin away.

76
00:06:05,360 --> 00:06:06,480
Come here.

77
00:06:06,560 --> 00:06:08,240
- No.
- Mr. Yai, please calm down.

78
00:06:08,320 --> 00:06:09,640
Mr. Yai.

79
00:06:09,720 --> 00:06:10,960
Let's talk it out.

80
00:06:11,040 --> 00:06:12,320
Please. Let's talk it out.

81
00:06:12,400 --> 00:06:13,280
Pin.

82
00:06:13,360 --> 00:06:14,760
Move.

83
00:06:15,520 --> 00:06:18,920
If you want to kill me, go ahead.

84
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:19,800
Do it!

85
00:06:20,400 --> 00:06:21,480
- Hey!
- Don't shoot.

86
00:06:23,120 --> 00:06:25,640
Mr. Yai. Auntie. Auntie.

87
00:06:27,920 --> 00:06:30,680
If you want to shoot me, then do it.

88
00:06:30,760 --> 00:06:31,560
Shoot!

89
00:06:34,240 --> 00:06:35,440
Mr. Yai.

90
00:06:37,680 --> 00:06:38,880
Stop it!

91
00:06:40,320 --> 00:06:41,600
Mom?

92
00:06:46,800 --> 00:06:48,080
- Auntie. Auntie.
- Madam.

93
00:06:48,160 --> 00:06:49,320
- Auntie.
- Madam.

94
00:06:57,480 --> 00:06:59,600
You already took my daughter away,

95
00:06:59,680 --> 00:07:01,520
and now you're trying to kill Madam?!

96
00:07:02,200 --> 00:07:04,960
If you want to take revenge on Madam,
it will be over my dead body.

97
00:07:13,640 --> 00:07:15,640
- Wait, Mom.
- Come here.

98
00:07:16,720 --> 00:07:18,400
Get down on your knees.

99
00:07:22,160 --> 00:07:23,280
Madam.

100
00:07:23,360 --> 00:07:25,920
I brought Pin here so you can punish her.

101
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:27,160
She's ungrateful.

102
00:07:27,240 --> 00:07:28,800
She went so far as to run away with a man.

103
00:07:28,880 --> 00:07:30,640
And it almost cost you your life.

104
00:07:33,240 --> 00:07:34,840
That's not it.

105
00:07:34,920 --> 00:07:36,280
That's not what happened, Mom.

106
00:07:36,360 --> 00:07:41,000
Well, Mr. Tong locked me up,
and Mr. Yai came to save me.

107
00:07:41,080 --> 00:07:42,520
And why didn't he bring you home?

108
00:07:42,600 --> 00:07:44,640
Where were you two all night?!

109
00:07:44,720 --> 00:07:46,760
Are you trying to say

110
00:07:46,840 --> 00:07:49,440
that I tricked you
into walking into Mr. Tong's trap?

111
00:07:49,520 --> 00:07:50,360
Pin.

112
00:07:51,360 --> 00:07:52,960
Just say it.

113
00:07:53,040 --> 00:07:55,240
Say it so your mother
hears it with her own ears.

114
00:07:56,600 --> 00:07:57,520
Well…

115
00:07:59,000 --> 00:08:02,240
We almost got killed by Mr. Tong's men.

116
00:08:02,320 --> 00:08:05,160
But Mr. Pan called Uncle Pload in
to help us just in time.

117
00:08:05,240 --> 00:08:06,520
Pload?

118
00:08:07,280 --> 00:08:09,120
Pan's father?

119
00:08:17,720 --> 00:08:19,760
What the hell are these?

120
00:08:19,840 --> 00:08:22,040
Oh? Didn't you order them online?

121
00:08:23,120 --> 00:08:24,320
You idiot.

122
00:08:24,400 --> 00:08:26,760
Are you crazy? I'm not dead yet.

123
00:08:26,840 --> 00:08:28,600
- Hey, open them.
- Yes, Boss.

124
00:08:47,840 --> 00:08:50,520
Hey, weren't you guys
supposed to butcher Yai?

125
00:08:51,160 --> 00:08:52,520
Why did it end up like this?

126
00:08:53,520 --> 00:08:55,120
TIGERS DON'T PREY ON THEIR OWN KIND

127
00:08:55,200 --> 00:08:56,160
<i>Tigers</i>

128
00:08:56,240 --> 00:08:58,120
<i>don't prey on their own kind.</i>

129
00:08:58,680 --> 00:09:00,840
<i>Consider us even this time.</i>

130
00:09:01,720 --> 00:09:03,960
<i>But if you still dare to touch Mr. Yai,</i>

131
00:09:04,040 --> 00:09:05,560
<i>prepare to count the bodies.</i>

132
00:09:06,080 --> 00:09:07,000
<i>Pload</i>

133
00:09:07,520 --> 00:09:08,840
<i>of Padang Besar.</i>

134
00:09:10,760 --> 00:09:13,120
Pload of Padang Besar?

135
00:09:13,920 --> 00:09:15,880
They were fully armed, Boss.

136
00:09:15,960 --> 00:09:18,200
Maybe they're a drug cartel
based near the border.

137
00:09:18,280 --> 00:09:20,400
They completely outgunned us, Boss.

138
00:09:23,840 --> 00:09:25,040
Damn it!

139
00:09:27,880 --> 00:09:29,720
They're operating a stone mine down south,

140
00:09:29,800 --> 00:09:31,240
not any kind of thieves' den.

141
00:09:31,840 --> 00:09:35,240
And Mr. Yai also
hasn't harassed me at all.

142
00:09:37,560 --> 00:09:39,600
Do people like Yai and Pan

143
00:09:39,680 --> 00:09:42,200
really have a legitimate business
as mine owners?

144
00:09:42,280 --> 00:09:43,480
I don't believe you.

145
00:09:47,320 --> 00:09:51,360
You fell for Yai so deeply and have
come up with this story to fool me? Huh?

146
00:09:52,440 --> 00:09:54,840
- Madam.
- Have you gone this far?!

147
00:09:55,880 --> 00:09:57,080
Pin.

148
00:09:57,160 --> 00:09:58,120
Come here.

149
00:09:58,200 --> 00:10:00,040
Come with me right now.

150
00:10:06,120 --> 00:10:07,320
Excuse me.

151
00:10:09,120 --> 00:10:10,280
MR. TONG

152
00:10:12,240 --> 00:10:13,360
Na.

153
00:10:14,080 --> 00:10:15,200
Leave me alone for now.

154
00:10:15,800 --> 00:10:17,640
Go get some rest upstairs.

155
00:10:19,520 --> 00:10:22,120
So… about Mr. Yai,

156
00:10:22,920 --> 00:10:24,320
what are we supposed to do?

157
00:10:25,680 --> 00:10:27,280
Don't worry.

158
00:10:27,800 --> 00:10:30,320
He wouldn't do anything to us right now

159
00:10:30,400 --> 00:10:32,640
since he has plenty of charges himself.

160
00:10:33,720 --> 00:10:36,040
And as long as I'm here,

161
00:10:36,120 --> 00:10:39,600
I'll never ever let anyone harm you.

162
00:10:57,160 --> 00:10:58,320
Mom.

163
00:10:58,400 --> 00:11:00,120
Please listen to me.

164
00:11:01,200 --> 00:11:02,240
Here.

165
00:11:02,320 --> 00:11:03,800
If your living here
is causing so much trouble,

166
00:11:03,880 --> 00:11:05,600
I'll send you away to live elsewhere.

167
00:11:06,200 --> 00:11:07,400
Mom.

168
00:11:07,480 --> 00:11:08,880
Please believe me.

169
00:11:08,960 --> 00:11:11,360
Mr. Yai really went
to save me from Mr. Tong.

170
00:11:11,440 --> 00:11:14,320
And he isn't even a thief.

171
00:11:14,400 --> 00:11:17,120
He has an engineering degree,
and he owns a stone mining business.

172
00:11:17,200 --> 00:11:18,320
Liar.

173
00:11:18,400 --> 00:11:19,760
I don't believe you.

174
00:11:20,560 --> 00:11:23,040
Did he force you to say that?

175
00:11:24,440 --> 00:11:25,600
Tell me.

176
00:11:25,680 --> 00:11:27,440
Has he already taken advantage of you?

177
00:11:27,520 --> 00:11:28,760
Mom.

178
00:11:29,320 --> 00:11:30,800
I have dignity.

179
00:11:31,560 --> 00:11:33,320
If he had really taken advantage of me,

180
00:11:33,400 --> 00:11:35,000
I'd rather be dead now.

181
00:11:36,320 --> 00:11:38,680
You said it like you don't know me at all.

182
00:11:40,840 --> 00:11:41,800
Mom.

183
00:11:44,240 --> 00:11:45,360
Mom.

184
00:11:47,920 --> 00:11:49,080
Mom.

185
00:11:49,680 --> 00:11:51,360
I swore, didn't I?

186
00:11:52,000 --> 00:11:53,320
I won't forget.

187
00:11:54,000 --> 00:11:55,920
Don't overthink it.

188
00:11:56,000 --> 00:11:57,680
Did you take your meds?

189
00:11:57,760 --> 00:11:59,040
Where are your meds?

190
00:11:59,760 --> 00:12:02,160
I'll go get them myself. Leave me alone.

191
00:12:13,680 --> 00:12:15,960
When Mr. Tong locked me up,

192
00:12:16,600 --> 00:12:18,640
I missed you the most.

193
00:12:19,960 --> 00:12:22,600
I was afraid to die
and not be able to see you again.

194
00:12:24,640 --> 00:12:26,560
I love you.

195
00:12:26,640 --> 00:12:28,600
Please don't be upset with me.

196
00:12:33,040 --> 00:12:34,560
If you love me,

197
00:12:35,320 --> 00:12:37,200
you have to love Madam too.

198
00:12:38,120 --> 00:12:39,840
Protect her.

199
00:12:41,120 --> 00:12:42,800
Don't let Yai do anything to her.

200
00:12:43,440 --> 00:12:44,520
Do you understand?

201
00:12:46,680 --> 00:12:47,640
Yes.

202
00:12:53,840 --> 00:12:55,640
What do I do?

203
00:13:00,040 --> 00:13:01,320
What do I do?

204
00:13:01,400 --> 00:13:02,680
Noi.

205
00:13:02,760 --> 00:13:05,120
- Noi.
- Huh? Pin.

206
00:13:05,200 --> 00:13:06,880
- What?
- Good thing you're here.

207
00:13:06,960 --> 00:13:08,400
Well, Mr. Na…

208
00:13:08,480 --> 00:13:10,440
- Mr. Na…
- Did he ask where I am?

209
00:13:11,840 --> 00:13:13,040
I saw Mr. Yai

210
00:13:13,120 --> 00:13:15,280
put Mr. Na in a headlock
and drag him somewhere.

211
00:13:15,360 --> 00:13:16,360
Huh?

212
00:13:21,800 --> 00:13:24,440
Mr. Tong wants to stay away from Yai

213
00:13:24,520 --> 00:13:26,760
because he doesn't want
to start a war with Pload.

214
00:13:29,560 --> 00:13:30,960
Damn it.

215
00:13:31,040 --> 00:13:32,280
What a coward.

216
00:13:32,360 --> 00:13:33,720
Thought you're a big shot.

217
00:13:34,320 --> 00:13:35,960
But you lost to a thug like Bandit Pload.

218
00:13:38,080 --> 00:13:41,320
So how many thugs
and bandits are there, really?

219
00:13:42,040 --> 00:13:44,960
And are you waiting for them
to come wipe out our entire family?

220
00:13:45,040 --> 00:13:46,880
Just shut up.

221
00:13:46,960 --> 00:13:49,040
If Yai really wanted to kill us,
he would have done so!

222
00:13:49,120 --> 00:13:51,320
He wouldn't let us
breathe freely like this.

223
00:13:52,880 --> 00:13:54,120
What if

224
00:13:54,200 --> 00:13:56,960
he was waiting for Na to come back
and take us all out at once?

225
00:13:57,560 --> 00:13:59,600
He despises Na.

226
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:16,160
I didn't expect you to change this much.

227
00:14:18,040 --> 00:14:19,600
It must be rough.

228
00:14:20,480 --> 00:14:22,040
If you need help with anything,

229
00:14:22,120 --> 00:14:23,400
please feel free to share.

230
00:14:30,520 --> 00:14:32,360
Who has it as good as you do?

231
00:14:32,880 --> 00:14:35,480
You always find a way
to be the center of attention.

232
00:14:45,160 --> 00:14:46,800
Are your hands weak or something?

233
00:14:46,880 --> 00:14:48,400
Hold it firmly.

234
00:14:48,480 --> 00:14:49,440
Whoa.

235
00:14:49,520 --> 00:14:51,800
You'd punch right into my handsome face.

236
00:14:51,880 --> 00:14:53,280
Can I try, Mr. Yai?

237
00:14:58,560 --> 00:15:00,640
Oh, my. Mr. Na!

238
00:15:01,320 --> 00:15:03,000
- Mr. Na.
- Na?

239
00:15:03,760 --> 00:15:04,800
Mr. Yai.

240
00:15:04,880 --> 00:15:06,160
Did you hurt my nephew?

241
00:15:08,200 --> 00:15:09,440
Madam.

242
00:15:09,520 --> 00:15:10,560
Yai.

243
00:15:11,080 --> 00:15:13,120
You're getting more and more violent.

244
00:15:13,200 --> 00:15:14,960
Apologize to Aunt Krong.

245
00:15:15,040 --> 00:15:17,520
I did nothing wrong. I won't apologize.

246
00:15:19,760 --> 00:15:20,720
That's true.

247
00:15:21,400 --> 00:15:23,640
Mr. Na wanted to play too.

248
00:15:23,720 --> 00:15:25,880
And the bag hit him in the mouth,
so he started bleeding.

249
00:15:25,960 --> 00:15:28,280
Mr. Yai didn't even do anything.

250
00:15:28,840 --> 00:15:30,240
Madam was the one…

251
00:15:31,520 --> 00:15:32,760
who was about to hit him.

252
00:15:33,480 --> 00:15:34,800
Is that true, Na?

253
00:15:38,160 --> 00:15:39,080
No.

254
00:15:39,920 --> 00:15:41,360
Mr. Yai punched me.

255
00:15:41,880 --> 00:15:43,280
And he was trying to punch her too.

256
00:15:46,960 --> 00:15:48,760
Mr. Yai probably didn't mean to do it.

257
00:15:48,840 --> 00:15:50,440
It's my fault.

258
00:15:51,160 --> 00:15:52,520
I wasn't careful

259
00:15:53,120 --> 00:15:54,760
and tripped over something myself.

260
00:16:00,280 --> 00:16:02,200
I'm sorry, Mr. Yai.

261
00:16:04,160 --> 00:16:05,960
If Na really bothered you,

262
00:16:06,480 --> 00:16:08,400
I'm so sorry.

263
00:16:11,080 --> 00:16:13,640
You'd better watch your back.

264
00:16:17,320 --> 00:16:19,360
Yai! What are you doing?!

265
00:16:20,040 --> 00:16:21,000
Apologize to her now.

266
00:16:22,080 --> 00:16:23,560
Go ahead and flog me.

267
00:16:23,640 --> 00:16:24,600
I did nothing wrong.

268
00:16:24,680 --> 00:16:26,040
I won't apologize.

269
00:16:29,720 --> 00:16:31,160
Yai!

270
00:16:32,040 --> 00:16:33,720
What's wrong with you, huh?!

271
00:16:35,640 --> 00:16:37,440
- Pin.
- Uncle.

272
00:16:38,400 --> 00:16:40,720
Please don't hit Mr. Yai.

273
00:16:48,000 --> 00:16:50,240
Un. Un, help me.

274
00:16:59,200 --> 00:17:01,240
Probably only Pinanong

275
00:17:02,160 --> 00:17:04,280
and Dad would believe whatever you say.

276
00:17:08,280 --> 00:17:10,119
Let's settle

277
00:17:10,200 --> 00:17:11,599
all debts and their interest today.

278
00:17:15,520 --> 00:17:16,839
What are you doing?

279
00:17:17,839 --> 00:17:19,680
I'm just spinning my gun around,

280
00:17:20,359 --> 00:17:23,520
but if it goes off at someone's head,

281
00:17:24,280 --> 00:17:26,000
let's just say their luck has run out.

282
00:17:26,599 --> 00:17:28,200
If they're dead,

283
00:17:28,280 --> 00:17:30,600
others can say anything, right?

284
00:17:35,560 --> 00:17:37,200
Uncle Paisal's spirit

285
00:17:37,880 --> 00:17:39,240
is probably watching us.

286
00:17:42,160 --> 00:17:43,880
Do you really want to disappoint him?

287
00:17:45,520 --> 00:17:47,440
He must want his only son

288
00:17:47,520 --> 00:17:48,880
to change and become a good man.

289
00:17:48,960 --> 00:17:50,600
Stop talking about my father!

290
00:17:53,000 --> 00:17:55,120
It's not too late for you
to change your ways.

291
00:17:56,600 --> 00:17:58,360
Whoa, don't! Help! Help!

292
00:17:58,440 --> 00:18:00,320
Mr. Yai! No, I'm scared now.

293
00:18:00,400 --> 00:18:02,160
- I'm scared! Help!
- Don't move! Stay still!

294
00:18:02,240 --> 00:18:03,240
Mr. Na.

295
00:18:19,160 --> 00:18:20,280
Blood?

296
00:18:21,560 --> 00:18:23,880
Mr. Na. Mr. Na!

297
00:18:23,960 --> 00:18:25,360
Mr. Na.

298
00:18:27,680 --> 00:18:28,600
Mr. Na?

299
00:18:30,960 --> 00:18:31,960
Mr. Na.

300
00:18:32,040 --> 00:18:33,880
Did Mr. Yai hurt you?

301
00:18:33,960 --> 00:18:35,120
Are you hurt anywhere?

302
00:18:42,520 --> 00:18:43,960
Please look up a little bit.

303
00:18:49,640 --> 00:18:51,000
Let's go to the hospital.

304
00:18:55,800 --> 00:18:56,880
It's okay, Pin.

305
00:18:58,720 --> 00:18:59,880
Think of it

306
00:19:00,800 --> 00:19:01,920
as just a nosebleed.

307
00:19:03,800 --> 00:19:05,880
Like I always had when I was young.

308
00:19:08,240 --> 00:19:10,240
Are you sure
you don't want to go see a doctor?

309
00:19:12,280 --> 00:19:13,600
The bleeding has stopped.

310
00:19:16,400 --> 00:19:19,200
Mr. Na, please forgive Mr. Yai.

311
00:19:19,280 --> 00:19:21,400
He deserves sympathy.

312
00:19:21,480 --> 00:19:22,840
He was forced to wander around.

313
00:19:22,920 --> 00:19:24,600
He must have been through
a lot of violence.

314
00:19:28,360 --> 00:19:30,080
I've never held it against him.

315
00:19:31,160 --> 00:19:33,280
I remember that
he was always bullying you.

316
00:19:34,200 --> 00:19:36,640
And you'd run to me, crying.

317
00:19:43,680 --> 00:19:44,840
Even nowadays,

318
00:19:45,760 --> 00:19:47,360
you're still the one

319
00:19:47,440 --> 00:19:50,760
who's always at the forefront of my mind.

320
00:19:53,160 --> 00:19:54,280
Me too.

321
00:20:19,600 --> 00:20:21,640
Do you still remember this?

322
00:20:40,360 --> 00:20:41,640
Wait for me, alright?

323
00:20:42,320 --> 00:20:44,640
Don't date anyone else.

324
00:21:04,240 --> 00:21:06,240
Take good care of our Indian cork tree.

325
00:21:29,680 --> 00:21:31,000
So beautiful.

326
00:21:33,320 --> 00:21:34,600
Just like you.

327
00:21:41,080 --> 00:21:42,520
Everything you've given me

328
00:21:43,600 --> 00:21:45,760
has always been invaluable to me.

329
00:21:46,840 --> 00:21:48,720
I carefully keep them all,

330
00:21:49,640 --> 00:21:51,560
including this Indian cork tree.

331
00:21:56,560 --> 00:21:58,200
You're impressive.

332
00:21:58,280 --> 00:22:00,280
You've managed to grow it this tall.

333
00:22:02,280 --> 00:22:05,440
What reward should I give you?

334
00:22:24,800 --> 00:22:27,000
A souvenir, for you.

335
00:22:27,600 --> 00:22:29,720
I've been carrying it
since I arrived in Thailand.

336
00:22:29,800 --> 00:22:31,280
I meant to give it to you

337
00:22:31,360 --> 00:22:32,600
the minute I saw you.

338
00:22:38,720 --> 00:22:40,240
I'm surprised.

339
00:22:40,320 --> 00:22:42,680
They sell hairpins there too?

340
00:22:46,760 --> 00:22:49,880
It's the only one
they had in the shop. Yeah.

341
00:22:49,960 --> 00:22:51,080
Do you like it?

342
00:22:52,360 --> 00:22:53,760
I love it.

343
00:22:54,520 --> 00:22:55,640
I really love it.

344
00:23:21,640 --> 00:23:22,600
- Gotcha.
- Oh?

345
00:23:22,680 --> 00:23:23,800
Whoa.

346
00:23:24,680 --> 00:23:26,320
- Mr. Yai.
- Hmm.

347
00:23:26,400 --> 00:23:28,720
Please give me back that hairpin.

348
00:23:28,800 --> 00:23:30,280
Why are you so possessive of it?

349
00:23:30,960 --> 00:23:32,720
A cheap hairpin like this?

350
00:23:32,800 --> 00:23:35,240
I can steal as many as you want for you.

351
00:23:35,320 --> 00:23:37,840
I don't need one from a thug.

352
00:23:37,920 --> 00:23:39,880
A thug?

353
00:23:40,520 --> 00:23:41,920
Who know full well

354
00:23:42,000 --> 00:23:43,440
who you hurt.

355
00:23:44,080 --> 00:23:45,320
Oh.

356
00:23:45,400 --> 00:23:48,080
So your beloved angel

357
00:23:48,160 --> 00:23:51,240
must have told you that I hit him
in the face so hard that his nose bled.

358
00:23:51,800 --> 00:23:54,160
Too bad. I should have cut
his tongue out too.

359
00:23:55,520 --> 00:23:57,520
I thought you'd be able to change.

360
00:23:57,600 --> 00:23:58,800
But no,

361
00:23:58,880 --> 00:24:00,360
you've never changed.

362
00:24:00,440 --> 00:24:02,280
You're the one who's never changed.

363
00:24:02,360 --> 00:24:04,880
You're still as gullible and deluded
by his words as ever.

364
00:24:05,840 --> 00:24:07,440
Stop talking about my father!

365
00:24:09,920 --> 00:24:11,880
It's not too late for you
to change your ways.

366
00:24:13,000 --> 00:24:14,200
Get out of my face.

367
00:24:28,040 --> 00:24:30,560
Still backstabbing like always,
you weakling.

368
00:24:30,640 --> 00:24:33,400
I really want to see
how you do in a fair fight.

369
00:24:37,480 --> 00:24:38,400
Come on.

370
00:24:39,240 --> 00:24:40,560
Punch me right here.

371
00:24:42,040 --> 00:24:43,440
What?

372
00:24:43,520 --> 00:24:45,240
Too scared to fight me head-on?

373
00:24:46,120 --> 00:24:46,960
Come at me.

374
00:25:18,080 --> 00:25:19,920
Whoa, don't! Help! Help!

375
00:25:20,000 --> 00:25:21,640
Mr. Yai! No, I'm scared now.

376
00:25:21,720 --> 00:25:24,360
- I'm scared! Help!
- Don't move! Stay still!

377
00:25:24,440 --> 00:25:27,040
You whine like a pig in a slaughterhouse.

378
00:25:27,960 --> 00:25:29,160
It's just a nosebleed.

379
00:25:29,680 --> 00:25:31,800
Hey, hey! Hey!

380
00:25:31,880 --> 00:25:34,440
Ugh, it's just a nosebleed.

381
00:25:39,440 --> 00:25:40,760
Can I have it back now?

382
00:25:42,280 --> 00:25:44,440
If you want it, come get it yourself.

383
00:25:48,320 --> 00:25:49,680
Mr. Yai. This hairpin

384
00:25:49,760 --> 00:25:51,360
is a gift from Mr. Na.

385
00:25:51,440 --> 00:25:53,880
It means the world to me.

386
00:25:53,960 --> 00:25:55,040
Mr. Yai.

387
00:25:56,320 --> 00:25:57,960
Please give it back to me.

388
00:25:58,560 --> 00:25:59,520
Alright.

389
00:26:05,640 --> 00:26:07,240
Go.

390
00:26:07,320 --> 00:26:08,560
It sank to the bottom.

391
00:26:09,720 --> 00:26:11,120
You're so cruel.

392
00:26:13,640 --> 00:26:14,760
Hey.

393
00:26:18,080 --> 00:26:19,560
How annoying.

394
00:26:26,640 --> 00:26:28,440
You'll never find it.

395
00:26:35,840 --> 00:26:36,760
Pin.

396
00:26:41,440 --> 00:26:42,480
Pin.

397
00:26:43,320 --> 00:26:44,400
Pin.

398
00:26:54,040 --> 00:26:55,240
Slowly, Pin.

399
00:27:01,200 --> 00:27:02,400
Mr. Yai?

400
00:27:03,160 --> 00:27:04,680
What did you do to her?

401
00:27:04,760 --> 00:27:06,320
Wait, Jom.

402
00:27:07,400 --> 00:27:08,720
He kidnapped you.

403
00:27:08,800 --> 00:27:10,200
Why are you still being nice to him?

404
00:27:10,280 --> 00:27:13,240
Mr. Tong was the one who locked me up.

405
00:27:13,320 --> 00:27:14,520
Without Mr. Yai's help,

406
00:27:14,600 --> 00:27:16,840
by now, he would have violated me.

407
00:27:19,840 --> 00:27:20,920
What did you say?

408
00:27:22,240 --> 00:27:23,920
Mr. Tong, the gambling den owner?

409
00:27:25,800 --> 00:27:27,120
Bastard.

410
00:27:27,200 --> 00:27:28,680
- I won't let you live!
- Hey.

411
00:27:29,320 --> 00:27:31,080
Don't act tough and throw your life away.

412
00:27:31,160 --> 00:27:32,520
Let go of me.

413
00:27:32,600 --> 00:27:33,840
You're just as vile.

414
00:27:38,760 --> 00:27:40,360
Enough, Jom!

415
00:27:41,240 --> 00:27:44,440
I really don't like
how you always talk with your fists.

416
00:27:47,160 --> 00:27:48,040
Pin.

417
00:27:49,680 --> 00:27:51,600
I'm just looking out for you.

418
00:27:52,200 --> 00:27:54,920
If you weren't the one,
she wouldn't bat an eye.

419
00:27:59,400 --> 00:28:00,320
Pin.

420
00:28:08,760 --> 00:28:09,560
Mr. Yai.

421
00:28:10,080 --> 00:28:12,000
Oh, Win?

422
00:28:14,720 --> 00:28:16,520
I've stayed at Paisal Farm all this time,

423
00:28:16,600 --> 00:28:17,560
waiting for your return.

424
00:28:18,840 --> 00:28:21,040
I've never believed
Paisal's son is a vile monster

425
00:28:21,120 --> 00:28:22,840
like everyone is saying.

426
00:28:22,920 --> 00:28:25,240
- But--
- I've disappointed you, haven't I?

427
00:28:26,920 --> 00:28:29,080
That's why I want to hear it from you.

428
00:28:29,160 --> 00:28:30,760
All the workers also want to know

429
00:28:31,440 --> 00:28:33,200
if they're being loyal
to the wrong person.

430
00:28:33,280 --> 00:28:35,400
What if I really am a murderer

431
00:28:35,480 --> 00:28:36,640
and a thief?

432
00:28:39,320 --> 00:28:40,880
I'll take you to the police myself.

433
00:29:12,800 --> 00:29:13,640
Mr. Yai.

434
00:29:14,160 --> 00:29:15,520
I'm sorry.

435
00:29:16,280 --> 00:29:17,520
I really am.

436
00:29:35,640 --> 00:29:36,680
Yes, On?

437
00:29:37,360 --> 00:29:38,840
How's your father doing?

438
00:29:42,280 --> 00:29:43,960
Why are you crying?

439
00:29:45,200 --> 00:29:46,280
Don't tell me

440
00:29:46,360 --> 00:29:47,640
your father…

441
00:29:48,680 --> 00:29:49,840
<i>Na.</i>

442
00:29:49,920 --> 00:29:51,920
<i>Can you come pick me up?</i>

443
00:29:52,000 --> 00:29:53,480
Wait, On.

444
00:29:53,560 --> 00:29:55,280
What's really happening?

445
00:29:57,760 --> 00:29:59,520
<i>Don't ask questions right now.</i>

446
00:29:59,600 --> 00:30:02,640
<i>If you love me,</i>
<i>please come pick me up now.</i>

447
00:30:04,360 --> 00:30:06,080
It's all your fault.

448
00:30:06,160 --> 00:30:09,080
You trusted your subordinates too much
and set up a company for them to run.

449
00:30:09,160 --> 00:30:10,760
And look what happened.

450
00:30:10,840 --> 00:30:13,720
When it collapsed, they all ran away.

451
00:30:14,240 --> 00:30:16,640
And if word gets out
about your bid-rigging,

452
00:30:16,720 --> 00:30:18,720
your career as Permanent Secretary

453
00:30:18,800 --> 00:30:20,320
will go up in smoke.

454
00:30:22,120 --> 00:30:23,440
That's enough.

455
00:30:23,520 --> 00:30:25,040
What's the point of saying that?

456
00:30:29,360 --> 00:30:31,640
Oh, where are you going, dear?

457
00:30:34,480 --> 00:30:36,040
I'll go see Na.

458
00:30:40,760 --> 00:30:43,400
You're going to borrow money
from Tatsana to help Dad, right?

459
00:30:44,160 --> 00:30:45,600
That's good.

460
00:30:45,680 --> 00:30:48,720
Na is the owner of a big farm.

461
00:30:48,800 --> 00:30:50,760
He should be able
to help us settle the debt.

462
00:30:51,600 --> 00:30:52,640
No need.

463
00:30:55,680 --> 00:30:57,800
Why would we need to beg others for help?

464
00:31:00,200 --> 00:31:03,280
We're on the brink of bankruptcy,

465
00:31:03,360 --> 00:31:05,720
yet you're still holding on
to your dignity?

466
00:31:08,000 --> 00:31:10,640
Dad's debt has nothing to do with me.

467
00:31:11,400 --> 00:31:13,520
And Na will never know about this.

468
00:31:13,600 --> 00:31:15,640
But our house is about to be repossessed.

469
00:31:19,800 --> 00:31:20,800
On.

470
00:31:20,880 --> 00:31:25,000
We paid for your school abroad,
and this is how you repay us?

471
00:31:26,320 --> 00:31:27,720
How could a farm owner

472
00:31:27,800 --> 00:31:29,600
be able to help us with our problem?

473
00:31:30,320 --> 00:31:31,760
I already told you that

474
00:31:32,360 --> 00:31:34,320
I'll handle this myself.

475
00:31:34,400 --> 00:31:35,840
You don't need to interfere.

476
00:31:41,160 --> 00:31:42,880
Please don't worry, ma'am.

477
00:31:43,440 --> 00:31:45,080
I'll go with Miss On

478
00:31:45,160 --> 00:31:47,600
and report everything to you.

479
00:32:02,280 --> 00:32:03,800
What's up, babe?

480
00:32:03,880 --> 00:32:05,400
You got the thing?

481
00:32:14,200 --> 00:32:18,640
Babe, you're the best in this whole world.

482
00:32:19,920 --> 00:32:20,960
You naughty woman.

483
00:32:21,760 --> 00:32:23,640
- She's going as far as doing drugs?
- Look at this.

484
00:32:31,840 --> 00:32:33,760
Here.

485
00:32:37,400 --> 00:32:38,760
I think

486
00:32:38,840 --> 00:32:42,680
we should go do
something fun outside the farm.

487
00:32:44,280 --> 00:32:45,240
Let's go.

488
00:32:47,720 --> 00:32:48,960
Don't you think

489
00:32:49,040 --> 00:32:50,840
doing it right here is more exciting?

490
00:32:51,600 --> 00:32:52,480
Huh?

491
00:32:55,080 --> 00:32:56,240
Are you crazy?

492
00:32:57,640 --> 00:32:58,600
Search everywhere.

493
00:32:58,680 --> 00:33:01,120
Someone reported a drug deal in this area.

494
00:33:01,200 --> 00:33:02,880
Catch them!

495
00:33:06,360 --> 00:33:08,760
- Open the door!
- Stop or I'll shoot!

496
00:33:11,800 --> 00:33:12,840
Bastard!

497
00:33:12,920 --> 00:33:14,400
Why didn't you wait for me?!

498
00:33:30,440 --> 00:33:32,280
- Put your hands in the air.
- I did!

499
00:33:32,360 --> 00:33:34,160
Hand over the evidence.

500
00:33:35,560 --> 00:33:37,480
Don't shoot me. Here, here.

501
00:33:37,560 --> 00:33:38,920
Don't shoot me.

502
00:33:41,240 --> 00:33:42,840
You're dealing narcotics

503
00:33:42,920 --> 00:33:44,560
without any fear of prosecution?

504
00:33:44,640 --> 00:33:47,200
It's not a narcotic.

505
00:33:47,280 --> 00:33:48,480
It's just makeup powder.

506
00:33:48,560 --> 00:33:51,160
It helps prevent acne on your face.

507
00:33:51,240 --> 00:33:54,720
I bought it online
from my friend just now.

508
00:33:54,800 --> 00:33:56,680
Caught red-handed like this

509
00:33:56,760 --> 00:33:58,440
and you're still making up stories?

510
00:33:58,520 --> 00:33:59,720
Spread your arms.

511
00:33:59,800 --> 00:34:01,200
Now.

512
00:34:01,280 --> 00:34:03,240
- Lift one leg up.
- Huh?

513
00:34:11,199 --> 00:34:12,840
You're this gullible.

514
00:34:13,520 --> 00:34:15,600
That's why you've ended up
as a slave to that junkie.

515
00:34:19,360 --> 00:34:20,639
Pan.

516
00:34:20,719 --> 00:34:21,880
You tricked me?

517
00:34:21,960 --> 00:34:24,360
You're smart now, huh?

518
00:34:24,440 --> 00:34:26,080
I thought your brain was just for show.

519
00:34:28,679 --> 00:34:30,159
Give me back my stuff.

520
00:34:30,239 --> 00:34:31,600
Aren't you ashamed of yourself?

521
00:34:31,679 --> 00:34:34,120
You're a burden to society
and a waste of space.

522
00:34:34,199 --> 00:34:35,760
Not only are you
throwing your future away,

523
00:34:35,840 --> 00:34:37,120
but you're also breaking
your parents' hearts.

524
00:34:42,920 --> 00:34:44,719
I don't have parents.

525
00:34:44,800 --> 00:34:46,480
The people who raised you

526
00:34:46,560 --> 00:34:48,280
are basically your parents.

527
00:34:50,040 --> 00:34:51,400
If you don't know anything,

528
00:34:51,920 --> 00:34:53,760
then don't judge me.

529
00:35:19,680 --> 00:35:20,600
Pin.

530
00:35:21,640 --> 00:35:23,800
- Mr. Na?
- So…

531
00:35:24,520 --> 00:35:26,920
I have some urgent business outside,

532
00:35:27,000 --> 00:35:29,480
but Auntie still
hasn't transferred me my salary.

533
00:35:29,560 --> 00:35:32,600
Can you lend me
4,000 or 5,000 baht for gas?

534
00:35:32,680 --> 00:35:35,560
I'll pay you back immediately
if I get paid tomorrow.

535
00:35:36,320 --> 00:35:38,120
No need to pay me back right away.

536
00:35:38,960 --> 00:35:42,400
I made some money selling plushies
and planned to send it to you,

537
00:35:42,480 --> 00:35:44,480
but you came back first.

538
00:35:45,960 --> 00:35:46,920
Here.

539
00:35:48,080 --> 00:35:49,200
So…

540
00:35:49,840 --> 00:35:51,960
you were selling stuff

541
00:35:52,040 --> 00:35:53,640
just to earn money for me?

542
00:35:54,680 --> 00:35:57,960
You got pickpocketed, so I got worried.

543
00:35:58,040 --> 00:36:01,280
I've been so worried about how
you'd get to school and survive each day.

544
00:36:10,480 --> 00:36:12,560
No matter how much time has passed,

545
00:36:13,080 --> 00:36:15,080
you've always been nice to me.

546
00:36:30,720 --> 00:36:32,640
Oh, Tawin. Good timing.

547
00:36:32,720 --> 00:36:33,720
Give me the car key.

548
00:36:34,360 --> 00:36:35,680
I'm afraid I can't.

549
00:36:35,760 --> 00:36:37,080
Mr. Yai asked me to bring you to him.

550
00:36:38,440 --> 00:36:40,200
But I have an urgent matter to attend to.

551
00:36:40,280 --> 00:36:41,960
He's waiting to start the meeting.

552
00:36:42,040 --> 00:36:43,600
We probably can't hold it without you.

553
00:36:55,360 --> 00:36:57,200
I've called for an all-hands meeting today

554
00:36:57,280 --> 00:36:58,320
because…

555
00:36:59,080 --> 00:37:00,280
Mr. Tatsana,

556
00:37:00,360 --> 00:37:02,920
my dear brother,

557
00:37:03,000 --> 00:37:03,840
has been the one

558
00:37:03,920 --> 00:37:06,320
to constantly remind me

559
00:37:06,400 --> 00:37:08,440
that I should act

560
00:37:08,520 --> 00:37:10,560
like an heir to Paisal Farm.

561
00:37:11,080 --> 00:37:14,320
So I decided to take my job seriously.

562
00:37:14,960 --> 00:37:15,960
And now,

563
00:37:16,560 --> 00:37:18,880
I will take control of all operations.

564
00:37:21,440 --> 00:37:23,240
And here

565
00:37:23,920 --> 00:37:26,840
is the list
of the employees' new positions.

566
00:37:28,320 --> 00:37:29,840
Mr. Pan.

567
00:37:29,920 --> 00:37:31,000
Would you read it aloud?

568
00:37:31,080 --> 00:37:32,440
Of course.

569
00:37:34,640 --> 00:37:35,560
Yai.

570
00:37:36,720 --> 00:37:38,040
Why did you write it upside down?

571
00:37:39,080 --> 00:37:41,320
You were holding it upside down. Here.

572
00:37:44,440 --> 00:37:46,400
The first one.

573
00:37:49,200 --> 00:37:50,400
Pan

574
00:37:50,480 --> 00:37:51,920
of Pa Hai?

575
00:37:52,000 --> 00:37:53,120
Pa Wai.

576
00:37:55,760 --> 00:37:56,760
Look.

577
00:37:56,840 --> 00:37:58,680
Your handwriting
looks like chicken scratch.

578
00:38:01,680 --> 00:38:03,080
The first one.

579
00:38:03,160 --> 00:38:04,720
Pan of Pa Wai

580
00:38:05,360 --> 00:38:07,240
will be the manager of the farm

581
00:38:07,320 --> 00:38:08,440
and the resort.

582
00:38:08,520 --> 00:38:09,560
Hey!

583
00:38:09,640 --> 00:38:10,840
How come?

584
00:38:10,920 --> 00:38:12,360
You're firing me all of a sudden?

585
00:38:12,440 --> 00:38:13,320
What did I do wrong?

586
00:38:14,280 --> 00:38:15,960
Don't misunderstand.

587
00:38:16,040 --> 00:38:17,800
I'm appointing you

588
00:38:18,520 --> 00:38:19,840
as a consultant

589
00:38:20,440 --> 00:38:21,320
to Pan of Pa Wai.

590
00:38:21,920 --> 00:38:23,800
If anything happens on the farm,

591
00:38:24,520 --> 00:38:26,720
just report it to let Pan know.

592
00:38:27,960 --> 00:38:29,360
Or…

593
00:38:30,400 --> 00:38:31,560
if there are any problems,

594
00:38:32,920 --> 00:38:34,600
you can object.

595
00:38:40,920 --> 00:38:41,760
None.

596
00:38:45,800 --> 00:38:47,320
Keep going.

597
00:38:47,400 --> 00:38:48,320
Ms. Tatsanee.

598
00:38:49,600 --> 00:38:51,200
You're going to be

599
00:38:51,280 --> 00:38:53,240
working as the secretary

600
00:38:53,320 --> 00:38:55,280
for yours truly.

601
00:38:55,360 --> 00:38:56,520
How?

602
00:38:56,600 --> 00:38:57,800
My family owns this place.

603
00:38:57,880 --> 00:38:59,080
Why do I have to serve you?

604
00:39:00,360 --> 00:39:02,280
Don't misunderstand, Nee.

605
00:39:02,360 --> 00:39:04,360
Pan has always lived in the woods.

606
00:39:04,440 --> 00:39:07,680
His English isn't strong enough
to handle foreign guests.

607
00:39:07,760 --> 00:39:10,640
You're probably better
at speaking English.

608
00:39:10,720 --> 00:39:12,880
So you don't waste time
doing pointless stuff too.

609
00:39:13,720 --> 00:39:16,040
- What? What?
- You!

610
00:39:16,680 --> 00:39:17,720
Nee.

611
00:39:22,560 --> 00:39:24,720
Yai has regained his farm.

612
00:39:24,800 --> 00:39:26,440
You'll walk away with nothing,

613
00:39:26,520 --> 00:39:27,840
not even a lump of soil.

614
00:39:27,920 --> 00:39:29,680
I'll never give him anything. Never.

615
00:39:29,760 --> 00:39:30,880
Never!

616
00:39:40,520 --> 00:39:41,840
What is it, Teera?

617
00:39:41,920 --> 00:39:43,880
Next,

618
00:39:43,960 --> 00:39:44,880
Mr. Tatsana.

619
00:39:46,600 --> 00:39:48,240
You will be

620
00:39:49,280 --> 00:39:51,640
working as a lead worker in place of…

621
00:39:51,720 --> 00:39:56,120
Mr. Tawi…

622
00:39:57,520 --> 00:39:58,800
Tawin.

623
00:39:58,880 --> 00:40:00,480
And Tawin will be working

624
00:40:00,560 --> 00:40:02,400
as workers' assistant
in place of Mr. Chalut.

625
00:40:03,160 --> 00:40:04,240
Chalit.

626
00:40:04,320 --> 00:40:06,040
Ugh, my name's Chalit.

627
00:40:06,600 --> 00:40:07,840
Alright, Mr. Chalit.

628
00:40:07,920 --> 00:40:09,320
Can you even do this? Give it here.

629
00:40:09,400 --> 00:40:10,240
I'll read it myself.

630
00:40:10,760 --> 00:40:12,960
I earned my MBA abroad.

631
00:40:13,480 --> 00:40:15,240
How could I be assigned
a job as just a lead worker?

632
00:40:15,320 --> 00:40:17,120
You've got an MBA,

633
00:40:17,200 --> 00:40:20,080
so it's only right for you
to manage the workers, Mr. Tsunami.

634
00:40:20,160 --> 00:40:21,520
Hey.

635
00:40:21,600 --> 00:40:23,240
It's Mr. Tatsana.

636
00:40:23,320 --> 00:40:25,440
His name is Tatsana.

637
00:40:26,760 --> 00:40:28,600
Or…

638
00:40:28,680 --> 00:40:31,080
do you not want this job

639
00:40:31,160 --> 00:40:33,720
because you're disgusted
by uneducated laborers?

640
00:40:40,360 --> 00:40:41,520
Well…

641
00:40:41,600 --> 00:40:44,200
I don't look down on people
because of their status.

642
00:40:44,280 --> 00:40:47,040
All the workers are like family to me.

643
00:40:49,320 --> 00:40:50,440
Well said.

644
00:40:50,520 --> 00:40:51,840
Then it's settled.

645
00:40:51,920 --> 00:40:53,320
A big hand!

646
00:41:02,040 --> 00:41:04,200
And you, Jom.

647
00:41:04,280 --> 00:41:05,840
You've worked here a long time.

648
00:41:05,920 --> 00:41:07,480
Lots of experience.

649
00:41:08,840 --> 00:41:10,240
Go be Mr. Tatsana's assistant.

650
00:41:15,200 --> 00:41:16,920
Of course, Mr. Yai.

651
00:41:17,000 --> 00:41:20,280
Jom and I will do our best for our farm.

652
00:41:25,040 --> 00:41:27,360
Last but certainly not least,

653
00:41:27,440 --> 00:41:29,280
we have…

654
00:41:29,880 --> 00:41:31,320
Mr. Jerd

655
00:41:32,240 --> 00:41:33,600
and

656
00:41:33,680 --> 00:41:34,720
Mr. Kan.

657
00:41:35,560 --> 00:41:37,960
You'll shift from being
Mr. Teera's assistants

658
00:41:38,040 --> 00:41:41,000
to being Piak's assistants.

659
00:41:42,960 --> 00:41:46,160
Consider Piak's words
my direct orders for you.

660
00:41:49,240 --> 00:41:51,720
Standing and talking too long
has made me sore.

661
00:41:52,960 --> 00:41:55,120
And for finance,

662
00:41:55,640 --> 00:41:58,800
who should I assign that to?

663
00:42:03,120 --> 00:42:04,480
Let's leave that vacant for now.

664
00:42:04,560 --> 00:42:05,480
Alright.

665
00:42:05,560 --> 00:42:06,600
Let's get to work.

666
00:42:07,200 --> 00:42:08,640
Meeting dismissed!

667
00:42:08,720 --> 00:42:09,960
- Yeah!
- Yeah!

668
00:42:22,360 --> 00:42:24,280
You couldn't hide your smile at all.

669
00:42:24,360 --> 00:42:27,160
I thought I was watching
a toothpaste commercial.

670
00:42:28,520 --> 00:42:29,840
Ever since Mr. Na's return,

671
00:42:29,920 --> 00:42:31,800
you've looked so happy.

672
00:42:34,360 --> 00:42:35,600
I'm not.

673
00:42:37,960 --> 00:42:39,800
Madam, the food is ready.

674
00:42:39,880 --> 00:42:42,160
These are all your favorites.

675
00:42:42,240 --> 00:42:43,160
I'm not eating.

676
00:42:43,240 --> 00:42:45,720
That sneaky thief
couldn't do anything to me,

677
00:42:45,800 --> 00:42:47,400
so he's trying to bully Na and Nee.

678
00:42:47,480 --> 00:42:48,400
I need to go take a look.

679
00:42:49,680 --> 00:42:51,480
Isn't Mr. Na going outside?

680
00:42:51,560 --> 00:42:53,440
- Oh, Aunt Un.
- Mom.

681
00:42:54,600 --> 00:42:55,920
Mom.

682
00:42:56,000 --> 00:42:57,720
Mom, sit down first.

683
00:42:57,800 --> 00:42:58,680
I'm okay.

684
00:42:58,760 --> 00:43:01,400
Just go help Madam and Mr. Na. Hurry.

685
00:43:01,480 --> 00:43:02,720
Go.

686
00:43:02,800 --> 00:43:05,000
- Watch her for me.
- Yes, Pin.

687
00:43:05,760 --> 00:43:06,880
Sit down.

688
00:43:06,960 --> 00:43:08,360
Easy.

689
00:43:13,200 --> 00:43:14,760
What is it you're doing?

690
00:43:14,840 --> 00:43:16,640
Where are Na and Nee?

691
00:43:17,240 --> 00:43:18,760
Just worry about this first.

692
00:43:18,840 --> 00:43:20,520
I'm getting rid of the evidence.

693
00:43:20,600 --> 00:43:23,760
Yai might come and ask
to see receipts or payout documents.

694
00:43:24,360 --> 00:43:25,520
We can't let him see any of it.

695
00:43:25,600 --> 00:43:28,880
Ugh, you think someone like him
knows about finance?

696
00:43:29,480 --> 00:43:31,120
He'll find someone else to audit.

697
00:43:32,200 --> 00:43:33,080
Shit.

698
00:43:34,280 --> 00:43:35,920
- Here.
- This one too.

699
00:43:55,440 --> 00:43:56,560
Ms. Nee?

700
00:43:57,160 --> 00:43:59,720
Ms. Nee. Have you seen Mr. Na?

701
00:44:02,120 --> 00:44:03,160
Ms. Nee.

702
00:44:03,240 --> 00:44:04,640
Why did you slap me?

703
00:44:05,800 --> 00:44:08,360
You're the one who told Yai
to go after me, aren't you?

704
00:44:08,440 --> 00:44:09,800
What did he do to you?

705
00:44:09,880 --> 00:44:11,880
He ordered Na to work on the farm

706
00:44:11,960 --> 00:44:14,080
and had me be Pan's lackey.

707
00:44:14,880 --> 00:44:16,200
Hey.

708
00:44:16,840 --> 00:44:18,720
Yai disappeared with you.

709
00:44:18,800 --> 00:44:21,320
And when he got back, he messed with me.

710
00:44:21,400 --> 00:44:22,840
You must have been
the one to convince him,

711
00:44:22,920 --> 00:44:25,440
because deep down,
you want to be on my level.

712
00:44:26,280 --> 00:44:27,480
No.

713
00:44:27,560 --> 00:44:28,600
Deep down,

714
00:44:28,680 --> 00:44:30,520
you want to outshine me,
don't you, servant?!

715
00:44:30,600 --> 00:44:31,520
Ms. Nee.

716
00:44:32,840 --> 00:44:34,760
If you're happy thinking that,

717
00:44:34,840 --> 00:44:36,640
there's no point in me explaining.

718
00:44:39,680 --> 00:44:41,160
Pan!

719
00:44:41,240 --> 00:44:42,680
Let go. Let me go!

720
00:44:42,760 --> 00:44:43,760
Okay.

721
00:44:45,200 --> 00:44:47,200
- You--
- Call me Manager

722
00:44:47,280 --> 00:44:49,560
if you don't want me
to tell your mom about the drugs.

723
00:44:50,400 --> 00:44:51,480
Go to the resort.

724
00:44:51,560 --> 00:44:53,480
I'll assign you some work.

725
00:45:36,160 --> 00:45:37,400
Mr. Na.

726
00:45:37,480 --> 00:45:39,280
If you can't stand the smell,

727
00:45:39,360 --> 00:45:41,640
I think you should take
a break over there.

728
00:45:41,720 --> 00:45:43,680
I'm not familiar with this climate yet.

729
00:45:43,760 --> 00:45:45,160
It's humid.

730
00:45:45,240 --> 00:45:46,400
Well then,

731
00:45:47,640 --> 00:45:49,240
I'll go get some fresh air over there.

732
00:45:55,920 --> 00:45:57,720
Where are you going, little bro?

733
00:46:00,080 --> 00:46:01,400
I'm going to get some water.

734
00:46:02,640 --> 00:46:04,920
I don't think you need mineral water.

735
00:46:10,080 --> 00:46:11,120
Jom.

736
00:46:11,200 --> 00:46:13,320
What have you trained my brother to do?

737
00:46:13,400 --> 00:46:16,200
Our jobs are to shovel the manure

738
00:46:16,280 --> 00:46:17,760
and wash the pens.

739
00:46:18,440 --> 00:46:20,920
I think Mr. Na should work in the office.

740
00:46:21,000 --> 00:46:24,160
I want him to learn
from the lower levels up,

741
00:46:24,240 --> 00:46:26,680
so people won't gossip

742
00:46:26,760 --> 00:46:28,640
that he's soft

743
00:46:28,720 --> 00:46:30,160
and can't even handle low-level jobs.

744
00:46:34,080 --> 00:46:35,200
Mr. Yai's right.

745
00:46:36,000 --> 00:46:37,280
I should do it.

746
00:46:38,760 --> 00:46:39,840
Go take a break.

747
00:46:49,320 --> 00:46:50,880
They're just pieces of manure.

748
00:46:50,960 --> 00:46:53,040
Look at it as a natural part of life.

749
00:46:53,120 --> 00:46:54,800
Just don't be a useless piece of crap.

750
00:46:54,880 --> 00:46:56,920
How's that? Do I sound witty?

751
00:47:14,560 --> 00:47:18,880
- Hey, hey. What? What now?
- Hey.

752
00:47:19,480 --> 00:47:20,840
You're out?

753
00:47:24,000 --> 00:47:26,840
I'd like to formally
welcome you to Paisal Farm,

754
00:47:26,920 --> 00:47:28,440
my beautiful soon-to-be sister-in-law!

755
00:47:29,120 --> 00:47:30,280
- Whoa.
- Na.

756
00:47:31,480 --> 00:47:32,600
On?

757
00:47:35,680 --> 00:47:40,040
I'm appointing Pin to lead the Accounting
and Finance Department of Paisal Farm.

758
00:47:40,120 --> 00:47:42,880
Pinanong was an accomplice
in extorting money from Paisal Farm.

759
00:47:42,960 --> 00:47:44,600
Pin might have gotten away,

760
00:47:44,680 --> 00:47:46,520
but don't think you'll walk free.

761
00:47:46,600 --> 00:47:48,560
I'll send all of you to prison!

762
00:48:28,440 --> 00:48:30,680
Subtitle translation by: Anan Pratchayakul
